NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 2] Missing leading-zero flag, counting 0-padded shorts as valid:</strong> Without leading flag, "007" is treated as 3-digit starting with 0, polluting bitmasks and adjacency checks. Fix: maintain leading = (all digits placed are 0). When leading=true, skip digit constraint.<br>\n'
NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 2] Caching tight=true across different bounds:</strong> tight=true depends on SPECIFIC upper bound. Running f(R) and f(L&minus;1) in same memo table contaminates results. Fix: two separate memo tables, OR only memoise tight=false (tight=true re-explored; only n positions).<br>\n'
NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 3] State explosion from large K (mod K with K up to 10&#8310;):</strong> 18 &times; 2 &times; K = 36M overflows memory. Fix: meet-in-the-middle &mdash; split digits in half; enumerate (prefix_mod, count) and (suffix_mod, count); join via hashmap in O(n/2 &times; K).<br>\n'
NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 3] Incorrect two-tight-flag transitions:</strong> When both tight_lo and tight_hi active, valid d &isin; [lo_digit if tight_lo else 0, hi_digit if tight_hi else 9]. Candidates forget to CLIP the lower bound. Fix: next_tight_lo = tight_lo AND (d == lo_digit); next_tight_hi = tight_hi AND (d == hi_digit).<br>\n'
NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 4] Applying digit DP for K-th valid number (construction):</strong> Digit DP counts; it does not construct. Fix: use digit DP as count function INSIDE binary search or greedy construction &mdash; try digits 0..9 in order, count completions, subtract until remainder found.<br>\n'
NEW += '                        &bull; <strong>[Stage 5] Not precomputing powers of 10 for sum DP:</strong> Contribution = d &times; 10^remaining &times; sub_count. Recomputing 10^remaining inflates constants. Fix: precompute pow10[0..18] before DFS.\n'
